My JavaScript function is supposed to return the largest number from an array but it's returning the wrong answer. Here's my code:

function findMax(arr) {
    let max = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        if (arr[i] > max) {
            max = arr[i];
        }
    }
    return max;
}

It works for [3, 7, 2, 9, 4] but not for [-3, -7, -2, -9, -4]. Why?
